dct_description_sm: compiled from the official records of the General Land Office, U.S. Coast & Geodetic Survey, U.S. Geological Survey, Canadian and other sources, under the direction of Harry King ; compiled and drawn by M. Hendges.
Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.
Shows land offices and reservations, transportation routes, mineral deposits, reported gold regions, isothermal lines, and religious missions by denomination.
Includes distance table and 2 inset maps: From Juneau to Forty Mile Creek. -- Continuation of Aleutian Islands.
From: Report of the governor of the district of Alaska to the Secretary of the Interior. 1903.
At head of title: Department of the Interior, General Land Office, Hon. Binger Hermann, Commissioner.
